.TH "ipr_sata_reset" 9 "ipr_sata_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipr_sata_reset \- Reset the SATA port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ipr_sata_reset
.BI "(struct ata_link *link "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *classes "  ","
.BI "unsigned long deadline "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
SATA link to reset
.IP "classes" 12
class of the attached device
.IP "deadline" 12
unused
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function issues a SATA phy reset to the affected ATA link.

Return value:
0 on success / non-zero on failure
